# Unit Tests

## Framework

- Node.js built-in test runner (`node:test`) + `node:assert/strict`
- Run: `npm test` (must pass before merge)
- Watch mode: `npm run test:watch`
- Runner: [scripts/run-tests.mjs](../../scripts/run-tests.mjs) discovers `tests/**/*.test.js`

## Layout

```
tests/
├── README.md               # index of critical gameplay validation tests
├── helpers/fixtures.js       # shared test maps and mocks
├── shared/                   # mirrors shared/ (+ shared/plugins/)
└── server/                   # mirrors server/ (+ app/, entities/, plugins/, config.js)
```

Mirror source paths:

| Source | Tests |
|--------|-------|
| `shared/plugins/combat/foo.js` | `tests/shared/plugins/combat/foo.test.js` |
| `server/plugins/combat/bar.js` | `tests/server/plugins/combat/bar.test.js` |
| `server/entities/Player.js` | `tests/server/entities/Player.test.js` |
| `server/app/gameLoop.js` | `tests/server/app/gameLoop.test.js` |

Legacy `tests/server/systems/` may still exist for modules re-exported from `server/plugins/` — prefer `tests/server/plugins/` for new tests.

## When tests are required

| Change | Tests |
|--------|-------|
| New pure function (pathfinding, combat, loot) | Required |
| Bug fix | Regression test required |
| Portal / pathfinding / zone travel | Test pure helpers in `shared/`; manual smoke for full flow |
| Socket handler / Express route | Integration test when feasible |
| UI-only render / audio change | Manual smoke test acceptable |

## Conventions

- One `describe` block per module; one `it` per behavior
- Use fixtures from `tests/helpers/` — avoid random data in assertions
- Test names describe behavior: `'findPath routes around obstacles'`
- No network or browser in unit tests; test pure logic and managers
- Mirror source paths: `server/plugins/combat/combat.js` → `tests/server/plugins/combat/combat.test.js`

## Example

```javascript
import { describe, it } from 'node:test';
import assert from 'node:assert/strict';
import { isWalkable } from '../../server/map/collision.js';
import { createSimpleMap } from '../helpers/fixtures.js';

describe('collision', () => {
  it('isWalkable returns false for water', () => {
    const map = createSimpleMap();
    assert.equal(isWalkable(map, 1, 1), false);
  });
});
```
